{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781368118682,"sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_D7qEHPAm0BFZ56ysYNejt12y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\n3: description: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n11: \n12: ## 2. TOPIC\n13: \n14: ui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n15: \n16: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n17: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n18: \n19: - [ ] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`?\n20: - [ ] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large?\n21: - [ ] Which scripts or search/generator mechanisms are useful enough to keep, and which are runtime/maintenance burden?\n22: - [ ] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill?\n23: - [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n24: \n25: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n26: \n27: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n28: \n29: - Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this packet.\n30: - Do not rewrite or re-derive the external repo data.\n31: - Do not evaluate `mcp-magicpath` except where it is already a related skill edge for `sk-interface-design`.\n32: - Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n33: \n34: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n35: \n36: - Stop after five iterations or earlier if all key questions have evidence-backed answers and remaining novelty is below threshold.\n37: - Stop immediately if research would require modifying target skill files or packet documents outside this lineage directory.\n38: - Stop with gaps if the external repo cannot be inspected locally.\n39: \n40: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n41: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n42: \n43: [None yet]\n44: \n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n46: \n47: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n50: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n51: \n52: - Reading root metadata, source-of-truth docs, and target skill docs separated reusable data assets from packaging-only surfaces. (iteration 1)\n53: \n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n55: \n56: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n57: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n58: \n59: - Exact initial glob of the expected external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; continue using the verified full external repo path. (iteration 1)\n60: \n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n62: \n63: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n64: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n65: \n66: ### Installer/platform-template direct merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempt)\n67: \n68: - What was tried: Treat external CLI and platform template plumbing as a direct merge candidate.\n69: - Why blocked: It serves external multi-assistant installation, while the house skill already has `.opencode/skills/` packaging and advisor metadata.\n70: - Do NOT retry: Direct CLI/marketplace plumbing merge into `sk-interface-design`.\n71: \n72: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n73: \n74: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n75: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n76: \n77: - Directly merging installer and platform-template plumbing; it adds maintenance burden without improving the target skill's design guidance. (iteration 1, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40)\n78: \n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n80: \n81: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n82: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n83: \n84: Inspect CSV data classes for content quality, overlap with existing design principles, and fit as references/data under `sk-interface-design`.\n85: \n86: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n87: \n88: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n89: \n90: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n91: \n92: - Packet spec states the external repo is MIT-licensed and includes styles, palettes, type pairings, product reasoning, UX guidelines, stack guides, BM25 search, and a design-system generator. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-61]\n93: - Packet scope requires per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP classification, house-structure mapping, licensing path, cross-lineage comparison, and negative knowledge. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:71-95]\n94: - `sk-interface-design` is currently a lean router plus one full principles reference, with `sk-code` implementation handoff and Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n95: - Memory context returned no prior packet-specific research results; this lineage starts from local source evidence.\n96: - resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n97: \n98: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n99: \n100: - Max iterations: 5\n101: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n102: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n103: - Progressive synthesis: true\n104: - Current generation: 1\n105: - Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z\n\n(End of file - total 105 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`?\n- [ ] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`?\n- [ ] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large?\n- [ ] Which scripts or search/generator mechanisms are useful enough to keep, and which are runtime/maintenance burden?\n- [ ] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill?\n- [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this packet.\n- Do not rewrite or re-derive the external repo data.\n- Do not evaluate `mcp-magicpath` except where it is already a related skill edge for `sk-interface-design`.\n- Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Stop after five iterations or earlier if all key questions have evidence-backed answers and remaining novelty is below threshold.\n- Stop immediately if research would require modifying target skill files or packet documents outside this lineage directory.\n- Stop with gaps if the external repo cannot be inspected locally.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n[None yet]\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Reading root metadata, source-of-truth docs, and target skill docs separated reusable data assets from packaging-only surfaces. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Exact initial glob of the expected external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; continue using the verified full external repo path. (iteration 1)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n### Installer/platform-template direct merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Treat external CLI and platform template plumbing as a direct merge candidate.\n- Why blocked: It serves external multi-assistant installation, while the house skill already has `.opencode/skills/` packaging and advisor metadata.\n- Do NOT retry: Direct CLI/marketplace plumbing merge into `sk-interface-design`.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Directly merging installer and platform-template plumbing; it adds maintenance burden without improving the target skill's design guidance. (iteration 1, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nInspect CSV data classes for content quality, overlap with existing design principles, and fit as references/data under `sk-interface-design`.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Packet spec states the external repo is MIT-licensed and includes styles, palettes, type pairings, product reasoning, UX guidelines, stack guides, BM25 search, and a design-system generator. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-61]\n- Packet scope requires per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP classification, house-structure mapping, licensing path, cross-lineage comparison, and negative knowledge. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:71-95]\n- `sk-interface-design` is currently a lean router plus one full principles reference, with `sk-code` implementation handoff and Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n- Memory context returned no prior packet-specific research results; this lineage starts from local source evidence.\n- resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":105,"totalLines":105,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781368118646,"end":1781368118680}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a024e1b960f201016a2d85368bb88191bb50464c6c322a16"}},"id":"prt_ec1d05d74001CWFF2FjV7G1OCo","sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","messageID":"msg_ec1d032b1001KtgJ13LE4vwLFB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781368118684,"sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oYdlO2UdFyYsElFzMTlx4onp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-001.md","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-001.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 1: External Repo Inventory And License Surface\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: Inventory the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repo structure, declared asset classes, installer shape, and licensing so later iterations can classify merge fit.\n6: \n7: ## Actions Taken\n8: \n9: - Read the packet spec for scope, success criteria, and source paths.\n10: - Read the external repo `README.md`, `skill.json`, `LICENSE`, `CLAUDE.md`, source-of-truth doc, and base templates.\n11: - Read the current `sk-interface-design` `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, `graph-metadata.json`, and principles reference.\n12: \n13: ## Findings\n14: \n15: - The external repo is materially a data-driven design-intelligence toolkit, not just prose guidance: its README advertises 67 UI styles, 161 color palettes, 57 font pairings, 25 chart types, 15 tech stacks, 99 UX guidelines, and 161 reasoning rules. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159]\n16: - The strongest merge candidates are the reusable data and reasoning assets, because the source-of-truth architecture explicitly separates `src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/`, `scripts/`, and `templates/`; generated platform folders and CLI assets are downstream packaging surfaces. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/CLAUDE.md:30-60]\n17: - The external package metadata confirms MIT licensing, broad platform targeting, and an installer-oriented distribution model, none of which directly matches the lean house skill shape. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:1-40]\n18: - The MIT license permits copying, modifying, merging, publishing, sublicensing, and selling, but requires preserving the copyright and permission notice in substantial copies. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13]\n19: - `sk-interface-design` is intentionally lean: the runtime `SKILL.md` routes design tasks to one full `references/design_principles.md` file and hands implementation to `sk-code`. A direct dump of the external skill content into `SKILL.md` would conflict with that structure. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n20: \n21: ## Questions Answered\n22: \n23: - Partially answered asset classification: data and reasoning assets are high-potential; CLI/marketplace plumbing is low-fit for direct merge.\n24: - Partially answered licensing: MIT content can be merged if notice/attribution is preserved.\n25: \n26: ## Questions Remaining\n27: \n28: - Which specific CSV/data classes should be ADOPT, ADAPT, or SKIP?\n29: - Should BM25 search and design-system generation remain runtime tooling, maintenance tooling, or be excluded?\n30: - What exact house directory layout should carry adopted assets?\n31: \n32: ## Ruled Out\n33: \n34: - Directly merging external installer/platform plumbing into `sk-interface-design`; the external repo is built to install across many AI assistants, while the house skill already has a native `.opencode/skills/` packaging model. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:254-293]\n35: \n36: ## Sources Consulted\n37: \n38: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-95\n39: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159\n40: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/CLAUDE.md:30-60\n41: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:1-40\n42: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13\n43: - .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17\n44: \n45: ## Assessment\n46: \n47: - newInfoRatio: 0.90\n48: - Novelty justification: First evidence pass established the repo's asset taxonomy, source-of-truth layout, installer split, target skill constraints, and license boundary.\n49: - Confidence: High for repo structure and license; medium for final classification until CSV/script contents are inspected.\n50: \n51: ## Reflection\n52: \n53: - What worked and why: Reading the root metadata plus source-of-truth docs separated reusable assets from packaging-only surfaces.\n54: - What did not work and why: The initial exact glob for the external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; future iterations should use the verified full path.\n55: - What I would do differently: Inspect representative CSVs and scripts next before making final ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP calls.\n56: \n57: ## Recommended Next Focus\n58: \n59: Inspect CSV data classes for content quality, overlap with existing design principles, and fit as references/data under `sk-interface-design`.\n60: \n61: ## Dead Ends\n62: \n63: - Installer/platform-template merge: skip direct adoption because house skill packaging already exists and platform bootstrap code would add maintenance burden without improving design guidance. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40]\n\n(End of file - total 63 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 1: External Repo Inventory And License Surface\n\n## Focus\n\nInventory the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repo structure, declared asset classes, installer shape, and licensing so later iterations can classify merge fit.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n- Read the packet spec for scope, success criteria, and source paths.\n- Read the external repo `README.md`, `skill.json`, `LICENSE`, `CLAUDE.md`, source-of-truth doc, and base templates.\n- Read the current `sk-interface-design` `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, `graph-metadata.json`, and principles reference.\n\n## Findings\n\n- The external repo is materially a data-driven design-intelligence toolkit, not just prose guidance: its README advertises 67 UI styles, 161 color palettes, 57 font pairings, 25 chart types, 15 tech stacks, 99 UX guidelines, and 161 reasoning rules. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159]\n- The strongest merge candidates are the reusable data and reasoning assets, because the source-of-truth architecture explicitly separates `src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/`, `scripts/`, and `templates/`; generated platform folders and CLI assets are downstream packaging surfaces. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/CLAUDE.md:30-60]\n- The external package metadata confirms MIT licensing, broad platform targeting, and an installer-oriented distribution model, none of which directly matches the lean house skill shape. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:1-40]\n- The MIT license permits copying, modifying, merging, publishing, sublicensing, and selling, but requires preserving the copyright and permission notice in substantial copies. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13]\n- `sk-interface-design` is intentionally lean: the runtime `SKILL.md` routes design tasks to one full `references/design_principles.md` file and hands implementation to `sk-code`. A direct dump of the external skill content into `SKILL.md` would conflict with that structure. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-001.md","text":"# Iteration 1: External Repo Inventory And License Surface\n\n## Focus\n\nInventory the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repo structure, declared asset classes, installer shape, and licensing so later iterations can classify merge fit.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n- Read the packet spec for scope, success criteria, and source paths.\n- Read the external repo `README.md`, `skill.json`, `LICENSE`, `CLAUDE.md`, source-of-truth doc, and base templates.\n- Read the current `sk-interface-design` `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, `graph-metadata.json`, and principles reference.\n\n## Findings\n\n- The external repo is materially a data-driven design-intelligence toolkit, not just prose guidance: its README advertises 67 UI styles, 161 color palettes, 57 font pairings, 25 chart types, 15 tech stacks, 99 UX guidelines, and 161 reasoning rules. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159]\n- The strongest merge candidates are the reusable data and reasoning assets, because the source-of-truth architecture explicitly separates `src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/`, `scripts/`, and `templates/`; generated platform folders and CLI assets are downstream packaging surfaces. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/CLAUDE.md:30-60]\n- The external package metadata confirms MIT licensing, broad platform targeting, and an installer-oriented distribution model, none of which directly matches the lean house skill shape. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:1-40]\n- The MIT license permits copying, modifying, merging, publishing, sublicensing, and selling, but requires preserving the copyright and permission notice in substantial copies. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13]\n- `sk-interface-design` is intentionally lean: the runtime `SKILL.md` routes design tasks to one full `references/design_principles.md` file and hands implementation to `sk-code`. A direct dump of the external skill content into `SKILL.md` would conflict with that structure. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n\n## Questions Answered\n\n- Partially answered asset classification: data and reasoning assets are high-potential; CLI/marketplace plumbing is low-fit for direct merge.\n- Partially answered licensing: MIT content can be merged if notice/attribution is preserved.\n\n## Questions Remaining\n\n- Which specific CSV/data classes should be ADOPT, ADAPT, or SKIP?\n- Should BM25 search and design-system generation remain runtime tooling, maintenance tooling, or be excluded?\n- What exact house directory layout should carry adopted assets?\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Directly merging external installer/platform plumbing into `sk-interface-design`; the external repo is built to install across many AI assistants, while the house skill already has a native `.opencode/skills/` packaging model. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:254-293]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-95\n- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159\n- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/CLAUDE.md:30-60\n- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:1-40\n- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13\n- .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17\n\n## Assessment\n\n- newInfoRatio: 0.90\n- Novelty justification: First evidence pass established the repo's asset taxonomy, source-of-truth layout, installer split, target skill constraints, and license boundary.\n- Confidence: High for repo structure and license; medium for final classification until CSV/script contents are inspected.\n\n## Reflection\n\n- What worked and why: Reading the root metadata plus source-of-truth docs separated reusable assets from packaging-only surfaces.\n- What did not work and why: The initial exact glob for the external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; future iterations should use the verified full path.\n- What I would do differently: Inspect representative CSVs and scripts next before making final ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP calls.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nInspect CSV data classes for content quality, overlap with existing design principles, and fit as references/data under `sk-interface-design`.\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Installer/platform-template merge: skip direct adoption because house skill packaging already exists and platform bootstrap code would add maintenance burden without improving design guidance. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":63,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-001.md","time":{"start":1781368118664,"end":1781368118683}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09a024e1b960f201016a2d85368bbc81918332f05bce634fc2"}},"id":"prt_ec1d05d850012Jz25qcGlRHyH8","sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","messageID":"msg_ec1d032b1001KtgJ13LE4vwLFB"}}
