ll-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/core.py\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/design_system.py\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/skill-content.md\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/quick-reference.md\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/platforms/opencode.json\",\".opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/references/design_principles.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Directly merge Phosphor icon imports\",\"reason\":\"It would introduce a library preference instead of preserving each app's existing icon system.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/icons.csv:1-28\"},{\"approach\":\"Directly merge React performance table into sk-interface-design\",\"reason\":\"Implementation performance guidance belongs primarily to sk-code.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/react-performance.csv:1-16\"},{\"approach\":\"Make external --design-system --persist workflow mandatory\",\"reason\":\"It writes project design-system files and conflicts with the house skill's lean prompt/reference shape.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/skill-content.md:77-109\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-13T16:32:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -15,11 +15,11 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n \n-- [ ] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`?\n+- [ ] What final house layout should carry adopted data and adapted guidance without making `SKILL.md` too large?\n - [ ] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large?\n-- [ ] Which scripts or search/generator mechanisms are useful enough to keep, and which are runtime/maintenance burden?\n+- [ ] Should stack-specific CSVs be adopted, adapted, or left to `sk-code` ownership?\n - [ ] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill?\n - [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n@@ -39,9 +39,10 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n-[None yet]\n+- Asset-class classification is mostly answered: adopt `products.csv`, `styles.csv`, `colors.csv`, `typography.csv`, `ui-reasoning.csv`, and `charts.csv` as data references; adapt `ux-guidelines.csv`, `landing.csv`, `design.csv`, `app-interface.csv`, quick-reference taxonomy, and optional lookup/generator scripts; skip direct Phosphor icon imports, direct React performance merge, and external platform templates. (iteration 2)\n+- Tooling fit is partially answered: `search.py`/`core.py` and `design_system.py` are useful optional lookup/maintenance tooling, but should not become a mandatory runtime workflow or persistence path. (iteration 2)\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n@@ -49,15 +50,18 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Reading root metadata, source-of-truth docs, and target skill docs separated reusable data assets from packaging-only surfaces. (iteration 1)\n+- Sampling CSV headers and representative rows produced a concrete per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix. (iteration 2)\n+- Locating actual `src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts` and `src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates` clarified that reusable tooling is separate from CLI/platform packaging copies. (iteration 2)\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n \n - Exact initial glob of the expected external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; continue using the verified full external repo path. (iteration 1)\n+- Looking for root-level `scripts/` and `templates/` failed; source-of-truth tooling lives below `src/ui-ux-pro-max/`. (iteration 2)\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n@@ -68,21 +72,43 @@\n - What was tried: Treat external CLI and platform template plumbing as a direct merge candidate.\n - Why blocked: It serves external multi-assistant installation, while the house skill already has `.opencode/skills/` packaging and advisor metadata.\n - Do NOT retry: Direct CLI/marketplace plumbing merge into `sk-interface-design`.\n \n+### Direct icon-library preference -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n+\n+- What was tried: Treat `icons.csv` as a mergeable icon guidance table.\n+- Why blocked: It encodes Phosphor-specific imports and would override each app's existing icon library or design system.\n+- Do NOT retry: Directly recommending Phosphor as the house default.\n+\n+### Direct React performance merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n+\n+- What was tried: Treat `react-performance.csv` as interface-design guidance.\n+- Why blocked: It is primarily implementation guidance owned by `sk-code`.\n+- Do NOT retry: Absorbing React/Next performance tables into `sk-interface-design` beyond design-relevant cross-references.\n+\n+### Mandatory external design-system runtime -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n+\n+- What was tried: Consider making the external `--design-system --persist` flow required.\n+- Why blocked: It writes project design-system docs and adds runtime/persistence behavior that conflicts with the lean house skill.\n+- Do NOT retry: Mandatory runtime persistence as part of the design skill.\n+\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n - Directly merging installer and platform-template plumbing; it adds maintenance burden without improving the target skill's design guidance. (iteration 1, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40)\n+- Directly merging Phosphor icon imports; preserve the app's existing icon system instead. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/icons.csv:1-28)\n+- Directly merging React/Next performance rules; keep implementation performance primarily under `sk-code`. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/react-performance.csv:1-16)\n+- Copying the giant generated `design.csv` corpus wholesale into `SKILL.md` or the main principles reference. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/design.csv:1-80)\n+- Making external `--design-system --persist` mandatory; it writes separate project docs and conflicts with the house skill's lean reference workflow. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/skill-content.md:77-109)\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-Inspect CSV data classes for content quality, overlap with existing design principles, and fit as references/data under `sk-interface-design`.\n+Map adopted/adapted assets into a concrete `sk-interface-design` house structure, inspect stack-specific guidance ownership, and define MIT attribution handling.\n \n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n","additions":30,"deletions":4},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-