rge into sk-interface-design\n - Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z\n - Status: IN_PROGRESS\n-- Iteration: 2 of 5\n+- Iteration: 3 of 5\n - Session ID: fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\n - Parent Session: none\n - Lifecycle Mode: new\n - Generation: 1\n@@ -25,47 +25,51 @@\n | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n | 1 | External repo inventory and license surface | research | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n | 2 | Data asset classification and script fit | research | 0.68 | 16 | complete |\n+| 3 | House layout, stack ownership, and attribution | research | 0.46 | 10 | complete |\n \n-- iterationsCompleted: 2\n-- keyFindings: 5\n-- openQuestions: 4\n-- resolvedQuestions: 1\n+- iterationsCompleted: 3\n+- keyFindings: 8\n+- openQuestions: 1\n+- resolvedQuestions: 4\n \n ## 4. QUESTIONS\n \n-- Answered: 1/5\n+- Answered: 4/5\n - [x] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`? Evidence: iteration 2 ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix.\n-- [ ] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large?\n-- [ ] Should stack-specific CSVs be adopted, adapted, or left to `sk-code` ownership?\n-- [ ] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill?\n+- [x] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large? Evidence: iteration 3 recommended house layout.\n+- [x] Should stack-specific CSVs be adopted, adapted, or left to `sk-code` ownership? Evidence: iteration 3 stack boundary classification.\n+- [x] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill? Evidence: iteration 3 mixed-notice path.\n - [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n \n ## 5. TREND\n \n-- Last 3 ratios: 0.90, 0.68\n+- Last 3 ratios: 0.90, 0.68, 0.46\n - Stuck count: 0\n - Guard violations: none recorded\n-- convergenceScore: 0.21\n-- coverageBySources: {external-root-docs: 5, external-data-csv: 12, external-scripts: 3, external-templates: 3, target-skill: 2}\n+- convergenceScore: 0.52\n+- coverageBySources: {external-root-docs: 5, external-data-csv: 12, external-scripts: 3, external-templates: 3, target-skill: 5, target-license: 1, sk-code: 1, external-stack-csv: 8}\n \n ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n \n - Installer/platform-template direct merge: skip direct adoption because it is external distribution plumbing.\n - Direct icon-library preference: skip Phosphor-specific imports as a house default.\n - Direct React performance merge: leave implementation performance to `sk-code`.\n - Wholesale generated design-system corpus merge: use selectively only.\n+- Wholesale stack CSV merge: most rows are framework implementation rules, not design direction.\n+- Single-license replacement: preserve both Apache-2.0 and MIT notices for mixed-source content.\n \n ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-Map adopted/adapted assets into a concrete `sk-interface-design` house structure, inspect stack-specific guidance ownership, and define MIT attribution handling.\n+Consolidate negative knowledge, check for contradictions across iterations, and decide whether convergence is reached before max iteration 5.\n \n ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n \n - Avoid bloating `SKILL.md`; adopted data should stay in references/data or optional tooling.\n - Keep implementation performance and stack-specific coding guidance aligned with `sk-code` ownership.\n - Preserve MIT attribution if any substantial external content is copied or adapted.\n+- Do not imply current `sk-code` supports stack routes it explicitly does not own today.\n \n ## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\n \n No blocked-stop events recorded.\n","additions":17,"deletions":13}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/skilled-agent