{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781368764941,"sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_A8xKKHCWUTvkn7IdtjKiLRXF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\n3: description: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n11: \n12: ## 2. TOPIC\n13: \n14: ui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n15: \n16: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n17: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n18: \n19: - [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n20: \n21: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n22: \n23: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n24: \n25: - Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this packet.\n26: - Do not rewrite or re-derive the external repo data.\n27: - Do not evaluate `mcp-magicpath` except where it is already a related skill edge for `sk-interface-design`.\n28: - Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n29: \n30: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n31: \n32: - Stop after five iterations or earlier if all key questions have evidence-backed answers and remaining novelty is below threshold.\n33: - Stop immediately if research would require modifying target skill files or packet documents outside this lineage directory.\n34: - Stop with gaps if the external repo cannot be inspected locally.\n35: \n36: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n38: \n39: - Asset-class classification is mostly answered: adopt `products.csv`, `styles.csv`, `colors.csv`, `typography.csv`, `ui-reasoning.csv`, and `charts.csv` as data references; adapt `ux-guidelines.csv`, `landing.csv`, `design.csv`, `app-interface.csv`, quick-reference taxonomy, and optional lookup/generator scripts; skip direct Phosphor icon imports, direct React performance merge, and external platform templates. (iteration 2)\n40: - Tooling fit is partially answered: `search.py`/`core.py` and `design_system.py` are useful optional lookup/maintenance tooling, but should not become a mandatory runtime workflow or persistence path. (iteration 2)\n41: - House structure is answered: keep `SKILL.md` lean, preserve `references/design_principles.md` as primary authority, and put adopted/adapted external content under an optional `references/design_intelligence/` subtree with a separate notice file if implemented later. (iteration 3)\n42: - Stack ownership is answered: skip direct stack CSV merge into `sk-interface-design`; adapt only cross-cutting design-quality fragments, and leave true implementation-stack adoption to future `sk-code` surface work. (iteration 3)\n43: - License path is answered: preserve the current Apache-2.0 Anthropic license/notice and add a separate MIT notice or license file for ui-ux-pro-max-derived content. (iteration 3)\n44: \n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n46: \n47: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n50: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n51: \n52: - Reading root metadata, source-of-truth docs, and target skill docs separated reusable data assets from packaging-only surfaces. (iteration 1)\n53: - Sampling CSV headers and representative rows produced a concrete per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix. (iteration 2)\n54: - Locating actual `src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts` and `src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates` clarified that reusable tooling is separate from CLI/platform packaging copies. (iteration 2)\n55: - Reading current target metadata kept the recommendation aligned with the lean house skill shape. (iteration 3)\n56: - Representative stack CSV inspection showed most stack guidance is implementation-specific and should not be absorbed into interface design. (iteration 3)\n57: \n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n59: \n60: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n61: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n62: \n63: - Exact initial glob of the expected external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; continue using the verified full external repo path. (iteration 1)\n64: - Looking for root-level `scripts/` and `templates/` failed; source-of-truth tooling lives below `src/ui-ux-pro-max/`. (iteration 2)\n65: - Treating stack CSVs as already owned by current `sk-code` failed because current `sk-code` does not support the generic React/Next/React Native/SwiftUI/Flutter stack routes. (iteration 3)\n66: \n67: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n70: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n71: \n72: ### Installer/platform-template direct merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempt)\n73: \n74: - What was tried: Treat external CLI and platform template plumbing as a direct merge candidate.\n75: - Why blocked: It serves external multi-assistant installation, while the house skill already has `.opencode/skills/` packaging and advisor metadata.\n76: - Do NOT retry: Direct CLI/marketplace plumbing merge into `sk-interface-design`.\n77: \n78: ### Direct icon-library preference -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n79: \n80: - What was tried: Treat `icons.csv` as a mergeable icon guidance table.\n81: - Why blocked: It encodes Phosphor-specific imports and would override each app's existing icon library or design system.\n82: - Do NOT retry: Directly recommending Phosphor as the house default.\n83: \n84: ### Direct React performance merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n85: \n86: - What was tried: Treat `react-performance.csv` as interface-design guidance.\n87: - Why blocked: It is primarily implementation guidance owned by `sk-code`.\n88: - Do NOT retry: Absorbing React/Next performance tables into `sk-interface-design` beyond design-relevant cross-references.\n89: \n90: ### Mandatory external design-system runtime -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n91: \n92: - What was tried: Consider making the external `--design-system --persist` flow required.\n93: - Why blocked: It writes project design-system docs and adds runtime/persistence behavior that conflicts with the lean house skill.\n94: - Do NOT retry: Mandatory runtime persistence as part of the design skill.\n95: \n96: ### Wholesale stack CSV merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempt)\n97: \n98: - What was tried: Treat external stack CSVs as mergeable `sk-interface-design` references.\n99: - Why blocked: Most rows are framework implementation checklists rather than aesthetic-direction guidance.\n100: - Do NOT retry: Moving stack CSVs wholesale into `sk-interface-design`.\n101: \n102: ### Single-license replacement -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempt)\n103: \n104: - What was tried: Consider treating the merged skill under one unqualified license label.\n105: - Why blocked: The current target carries Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution and external MIT material requires preserving a separate copyright/permission notice.\n106: - Do NOT retry: Replacing Apache-2.0 or MIT notices with a single generic statement.\n107: \n108: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n109: \n110: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n111: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n112: \n113: - Directly merging installer and platform-template plumbing; it adds maintenance burden without improving the target skill's design guidance. (iteration 1, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40)\n114: - Directly merging Phosphor icon imports; preserve the app's existing icon system instead. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/icons.csv:1-28)\n115: - Directly merging React/Next performance rules; keep implementation performance primarily under `sk-code`. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/react-performance.csv:1-16)\n116: - Copying the giant generated `design.csv` corpus wholesale into `SKILL.md` or the main principles reference. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/design.csv:1-80)\n117: - Making external `--design-system --persist` mandatory; it writes separate project docs and conflicts with the house skill's lean reference workflow. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/skill-content.md:77-109)\n118: - Moving stack CSVs wholesale into `sk-interface-design`; most content belongs to implementation-stack guidance or future `sk-code` expansion. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/stacks/react.csv:1-54)\n119: - Treating current `sk-code` as already covering all external stack CSVs. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:240-245)\n120: - Replacing existing Apache-2.0 notices or external MIT notices with one unqualified license statement. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/LICENSE.txt:90-122)\n121: \n122: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: \n124: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n125: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n126: \n127: Consolidate negative knowledge, check for contradictions across iterations, and decide whether convergence is reached before max iteration 5.\n128: \n129: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n130: \n131: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n132: \n133: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n134: \n135: - Packet spec states the external repo is MIT-licensed and includes styles, palettes, type pairings, product reasoning, UX guidelines, stack guides, BM25 search, and a design-system generator. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-61]\n136: - Packet scope requires per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP classification, house-structure mapping, licensing path, cross-lineage comparison, and negative knowledge. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:71-95]\n137: - `sk-interface-design` is currently a lean router plus one full principles reference, with `sk-code` implementation handoff and Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n138: - Memory context returned no prior packet-specific research results; this lineage starts from local source evidence.\n139: - resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n140: \n141: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n142: \n143: - Max iterations: 5\n144: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n145: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n146: - Progressive synthesis: true\n147: - Current generation: 1\n148: - Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z\n\n(End of file - total 148 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Runtime strategy for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage researching ui-ux-pro-max merge recommendations for sk-interface-design.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast Lineage\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis lineage investigates how the vendored `ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main` repository can improve `sk-interface-design` without bloating the house skill or changing implementation in this research packet.\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this packet.\n- Do not rewrite or re-derive the external repo data.\n- Do not evaluate `mcp-magicpath` except where it is already a related skill edge for `sk-interface-design`.\n- Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Stop after five iterations or earlier if all key questions have evidence-backed answers and remaining novelty is below threshold.\n- Stop immediately if research would require modifying target skill files or packet documents outside this lineage directory.\n- Stop with gaps if the external repo cannot be inspected locally.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- Asset-class classification is mostly answered: adopt `products.csv`, `styles.csv`, `colors.csv`, `typography.csv`, `ui-reasoning.csv`, and `charts.csv` as data references; adapt `ux-guidelines.csv`, `landing.csv`, `design.csv`, `app-interface.csv`, quick-reference taxonomy, and optional lookup/generator scripts; skip direct Phosphor icon imports, direct React performance merge, and external platform templates. (iteration 2)\n- Tooling fit is partially answered: `search.py`/`core.py` and `design_system.py` are useful optional lookup/maintenance tooling, but should not become a mandatory runtime workflow or persistence path. (iteration 2)\n- House structure is answered: keep `SKILL.md` lean, preserve `references/design_principles.md` as primary authority, and put adopted/adapted external content under an optional `references/design_intelligence/` subtree with a separate notice file if implemented later. (iteration 3)\n- Stack ownership is answered: skip direct stack CSV merge into `sk-interface-design`; adapt only cross-cutting design-quality fragments, and leave true implementation-stack adoption to future `sk-code` surface work. (iteration 3)\n- License path is answered: preserve the current Apache-2.0 Anthropic license/notice and add a separate MIT notice or license file for ui-ux-pro-max-derived content. (iteration 3)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Reading root metadata, source-of-truth docs, and target skill docs separated reusable data assets from packaging-only surfaces. (iteration 1)\n- Sampling CSV headers and representative rows produced a concrete per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix. (iteration 2)\n- Locating actual `src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts` and `src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates` clarified that reusable tooling is separate from CLI/platform packaging copies. (iteration 2)\n- Reading current target metadata kept the recommendation aligned with the lean house skill shape. (iteration 3)\n- Representative stack CSV inspection showed most stack guidance is implementation-specific and should not be absorbed into interface design. (iteration 3)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Exact initial glob of the expected external path returned no files until the broader packet tree was listed; continue using the verified full external repo path. (iteration 1)\n- Looking for root-level `scripts/` and `templates/` failed; source-of-truth tooling lives below `src/ui-ux-pro-max/`. (iteration 2)\n- Treating stack CSVs as already owned by current `sk-code` failed because current `sk-code` does not support the generic React/Next/React Native/SwiftUI/Flutter stack routes. (iteration 3)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n### Installer/platform-template direct merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Treat external CLI and platform template plumbing as a direct merge candidate.\n- Why blocked: It serves external multi-assistant installation, while the house skill already has `.opencode/skills/` packaging and advisor metadata.\n- Do NOT retry: Direct CLI/marketplace plumbing merge into `sk-interface-design`.\n\n### Direct icon-library preference -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Treat `icons.csv` as a mergeable icon guidance table.\n- Why blocked: It encodes Phosphor-specific imports and would override each app's existing icon library or design system.\n- Do NOT retry: Directly recommending Phosphor as the house default.\n\n### Direct React performance merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Treat `react-performance.csv` as interface-design guidance.\n- Why blocked: It is primarily implementation guidance owned by `sk-code`.\n- Do NOT retry: Absorbing React/Next performance tables into `sk-interface-design` beyond design-relevant cross-references.\n\n### Mandatory external design-system runtime -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Consider making the external `--design-system --persist` flow required.\n- Why blocked: It writes project design-system docs and adds runtime/persistence behavior that conflicts with the lean house skill.\n- Do NOT retry: Mandatory runtime persistence as part of the design skill.\n\n### Wholesale stack CSV merge -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Treat external stack CSVs as mergeable `sk-interface-design` references.\n- Why blocked: Most rows are framework implementation checklists rather than aesthetic-direction guidance.\n- Do NOT retry: Moving stack CSVs wholesale into `sk-interface-design`.\n\n### Single-license replacement -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempt)\n\n- What was tried: Consider treating the merged skill under one unqualified license label.\n- Why blocked: The current target carries Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution and external MIT material requires preserving a separate copyright/permission notice.\n- Do NOT retry: Replacing Apache-2.0 or MIT notices with a single generic statement.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Directly merging installer and platform-template plumbing; it adds maintenance burden without improving the target skill's design guidance. (iteration 1, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/skill.json:20-40)\n- Directly merging Phosphor icon imports; preserve the app's existing icon system instead. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/icons.csv:1-28)\n- Directly merging React/Next performance rules; keep implementation performance primarily under `sk-code`. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/react-performance.csv:1-16)\n- Copying the giant generated `design.csv` corpus wholesale into `SKILL.md` or the main principles reference. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/design.csv:1-80)\n- Making external `--design-system --persist` mandatory; it writes separate project docs and conflicts with the house skill's lean reference workflow. (iteration 2, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/skill-content.md:77-109)\n- Moving stack CSVs wholesale into `sk-interface-design`; most content belongs to implementation-stack guidance or future `sk-code` expansion. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/stacks/react.csv:1-54)\n- Treating current `sk-code` as already covering all external stack CSVs. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:240-245)\n- Replacing existing Apache-2.0 notices or external MIT notices with one unqualified license statement. (iteration 3, evidence: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/LICENSE.txt:90-122)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nConsolidate negative knowledge, check for contradictions across iterations, and decide whether convergence is reached before max iteration 5.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Packet spec states the external repo is MIT-licensed and includes styles, palettes, type pairings, product reasoning, UX guidelines, stack guides, BM25 search, and a design-system generator. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:55-61]\n- Packet scope requires per-asset ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP classification, house-structure mapping, licensing path, cross-lineage comparison, and negative knowledge. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/spec.md:71-95]\n- `sk-interface-design` is currently a lean router plus one full principles reference, with `sk-code` implementation handoff and Apache-2.0 Anthropic attribution. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:14-17]\n- Memory context returned no prior packet-specific research results; this lineage starts from local source evidence.\n- resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":148,"totalLines":148,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781368764925,"end":1781368764939}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f19db1650645d89016a2d87bcc3ec8191aefca6e50c9232d4"}},"id":"prt_ec1da39bc00183hXUFMdBwNu7v","sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","messageID":"msg_ec1da0a4f001NLmUhiCPthNdK6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781368765093,"sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oZcZRJHKMITBSvWNh5PndCtB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\",\n3:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n4:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n5:   \"generation\": 1,\n6:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n7:   \"terminalStop\": null,\n8:   \"openQuestions\": [\n9:     {\n10:       \"id\": \"question-5-negative-knowledge\",\n11:       \"text\": \"What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\",\n12:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n13:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n14:     }\n15:   ],\n16:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n17:     {\n18:       \"id\": \"question-1-asset-classification\",\n19:       \"text\": \"Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for sk-interface-design?\",\n20:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n21:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 2,\n22:       \"answer\": \"Adopt core data references; adapt QA, landing, mobile, generated examples, quick-reference taxonomy, and optional search/generator tooling; skip direct icon-library preference, direct React performance merge, and external templates.\"\n23:     },\n24:     {\n25:       \"id\": \"question-2-house-structure\",\n26:       \"text\": \"How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making SKILL.md too large?\",\n27:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n28:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3,\n29:       \"answer\": \"Keep SKILL.md lean, keep design_principles.md primary, and add optional references/design_intelligence assets plus notices if implemented later.\"\n30:     },\n31:     {\n32:       \"id\": \"question-3-stack-ownership\",\n33:       \"text\": \"Should stack-specific CSVs be adopted, adapted, or left to sk-code ownership?\",\n34:       \"addedAtIteration\": 2,\n35:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3,\n36:       \"answer\": \"Skip direct stack CSV merge into sk-interface-design; adapt only cross-cutting design quality fragments and leave real implementation-stack adoption to future sk-code surface work.\"\n37:     },\n38:     {\n39:       \"id\": \"question-4-license-attribution\",\n40:       \"text\": \"What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill?\",\n41:       \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n42:       \"resolvedAtIteration\": 3,\n43:       \"answer\": \"Preserve existing Apache-2.0 attribution and add a separate MIT notice/license file for ui-ux-pro-max-derived content.\"\n44:     }\n45:   ],\n46:   \"keyFindings\": [\n47:     {\n48:       \"id\": \"f-iter001-asset-taxonomy\",\n49:       \"iteration\": 1,\n50:       \"summary\": \"External repo is a data-driven design intelligence toolkit with styles, colors, typography, UX, chart, stack, and reasoning datasets.\",\n51:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/README.md:151-159\"\n52:     },\n53:     {\n54:       \"id\": \"f-iter001-mit-license\",\n55:       \"iteration\": 1,\n56:       \"summary\": \"MIT content can be merged or adapted if copyright and permission notices are preserved.\",\n57:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13\"\n58:     },\n59:     {\n60:       \"id\": \"f-iter002-adopt-core-data\",\n61:       \"iteration\": 2,\n62:       \"summary\": \"products, styles, colors, typography, ui-reasoning, and charts are strong ADOPT candidates as data references rather than SKILL.md prose.\",\n63:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/data/styles.csv:1-10\"\n64:     },\n65:     {\n66:       \"id\": \"f-iter002-adapt-qa-patterns\",\n67:       \"iteration\": 2,\n68:       \"summary\": \"ux-guidelines, landing, app-interface, design.csv, and quick-reference content are useful but need adaptation, compression, and house-style framing.\",\n69:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/templates/base/quick-reference.md:39-54\"\n70:     },\n71:     {\n72:       \"id\": \"f-iter002-scripts-optional\",\n73:       \"iteration\": 2,\n74:       \"summary\": \"search.py/core.py and design_system.py are useful optional lookup/generation tooling, not mandatory runtime workflow for every design task.\",\n75:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/src/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py:56-114\"\n76:     },\n77:     {\n78:       \"id\": \"f-iter003-lean-layout\",\n79:       \"iteration\": 3,\n80:       \"summary\": \"Future merge should keep SKILL.md lean and add optional references/design_intelligence assets rather than replacing design_principles.md.\",\n81:       \"source\": \".opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/SKILL.md:65-82\"\n82:     },\n83:     {\n84:       \"id\": \"f-iter003-stack-boundary\",\n85:       \"iteration\": 3,\n86:       \"summary\": \"Stack CSVs are mostly implementation checklists; skip direct merge into sk-interface-design and leave true stack adoption to future sk-code surface expansion.\",\n87:       \"source\": \".opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:240-245\"\n88:     },\n89:     {\n90:       \"id\": \"f-iter003-license-path\",\n91:       \"iteration\": 3,\n92:       \"summary\": \"Mixed-source merge requires preserving the existing Apache-2.0 notice and adding a separate MIT notice/file for ui-ux-pro-max-derived content.\",\n93:       \"source\": \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/external/ui-ux-pro-max-skill-main/LICENSE:1-13\"\n94:     }\n95:   ],\n96:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n97:     {\n98:       \"direction\": \"Installer/platform-template direct merge\",\n99:       \"iteration\": 1,\n100:       \"reason\": \"Packaging plumbing does not improve sk-interface-design guidance and conflicts with lean house packaging.\"\n101:     },\n102:     {\n103:       \"direction\": \"Direct icon-library preference\",\n104:       \"iteration\": 2,\n105:       \"reason\": \"Phosphor-specific imports should not override the app's existing icon system.\"\n106:     },\n107:     {\n108:       \"direction\": \"Direct React performance merge\",\n109:       \"iteration\": 2,\n110:       \"reason\": \"Performance/code implementation guidance belongs to sk-code.\"\n111:     },\n112:     {\n113:       \"direction\": \"Wholesale generated design-system corpus merge\",\n114:       \"iteration\": 2,\n115:       \"reason\": \"The giant design.csv corpus would bloat the lean house skill and undermine brief-specific critique.\"\n116:     },\n117:     {\n118:       \"direction\": \"Wholesale stack CSV merge\",\n119:       \"iteration\": 3,\n120:       \"reason\": \"Most stack guidance is framework implementation, not design direction.\"\n121:     },\n122:     {\n123:       \"direction\": \"Single-license replacement\",\n124:       \"iteration\": 3,\n125:       \"reason\": \"Apache-2.0 and MIT notices both need preservation for mixed-source content.\"\n126:     }\n127:   ],\n128:   \"metrics\": {\n129:     \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n130:     \"openQuestions\": 1,\n131:     \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n132:     \"keyFindings\": 8,\n133:     \"convergenceScore\": 0.52,\n134:     \"coverageBySources\": {\n135:       \"external-root-docs\": 5,\n136:       \"external-data-csv\": 12,\n137:       \"external-scripts\": 3,\n138:       \"external-templates\": 3,\n139:       \"target-skill\": 5,\n140:       \"target-license\": 1,\n141:       \"sk-code\": 1,\n142:       \"external-stack-csv\": 8\n143:     }\n144:   },\n145:   \"status\": \"IN_PROGRESS\",\n146:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n147: }\n\n(End of file - total 147 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-negative-knowledge\",\n      \"text\": \"What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,\n      \"resolvedAtIteration\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-1-asset-classification\",\n      \"text\": \"Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for sk-interface-design?\",\n      \"addedAtIteration\": 0,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"terminalStop\": null,\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"question-5-negative-knowledge\",\n      \"text\": \"What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-