ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-004.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-004.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,81 @@\n+# Iteration 4: Convergence And Negative Knowledge\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Consolidate the final negative knowledge and merge-risk list, then determine whether further iterations are likely to add enough new information to justify running to iteration 5.\n+\n+## Actions Taken\n+\n+- Read the current state log, strategy, findings registry, and prior iteration reports.\n+- Checked the open questions against answered questions and ruled-out directions.\n+- Compared iteration 2 asset classification with iteration 3 structure, stack ownership, and attribution recommendations.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+- No contradiction was found between the asset classification and the house-structure recommendation. Iteration 2 says high-value external content should be adopted as data/reference assets, and iteration 3 gives that content a separate optional `references/design_intelligence/` subtree rather than changing the primary design process. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:34-53] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:29-52]\n+- No contradiction was found between script adaptation and runtime restraint. Iteration 2 classifies search/generator scripts as optional tooling; iteration 3 says runtime routing should not make Python search or generator execution mandatory. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:29-31] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:20-21]\n+- No contradiction was found between stack guidance value and ownership. Iteration 2 already skipped direct React performance merge; iteration 3 broadened that into a stack-boundary rule after checking representative stack CSVs and current `sk-code` scope. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:27-28] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:22-25]\n+- The final negative knowledge is stable: do not merge external installer/platform plumbing; do not dump data into `SKILL.md`; do not replace `design_principles.md`; do not make external generators mandatory; do not prefer Phosphor icons; do not absorb React/stack implementation rules into `sk-interface-design`; do not assume current `sk-code` owns generic stacks; do not collapse Apache-2.0 and MIT notices. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:72-120]\n+- The only residual uncertainty is naming, not substance: a future implementation packet can choose exact names (`references/design_intelligence/`, `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`, `scripts/design_lookup.py`) while preserving the same architectural recommendation. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:29-52]\n+\n+## Final Negative Knowledge\n+\n+- Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this research lineage.\n+- Do not merge the external installer, marketplace, CLI, or platform-template plumbing.\n+- Do not inline large CSVs or generated design-system text into `SKILL.md`.\n+- Do not replace the Anthropic-derived `references/design_principles.md`; keep it as the primary authority.\n+- Do not make `search.py`, `core.py`, or `design_system.py` mandatory runtime steps.\n+- Do not use `design_system.py --persist` as a default house workflow because it writes separate design-system documents.\n+- Do not make Phosphor the default icon system for all projects.\n+- Do not absorb React/Next/React Native/SwiftUI/Flutter implementation checklists into `sk-interface-design`.\n+- Do not imply current `sk-code` already supports those generic stack routes.\n+- Do not use `ui-reasoning.csv` as deterministic truth; it should guide, not override the brief and critique process.\n+- Do not collapse Apache-2.0 and MIT material under one unqualified license label.\n+\n+## Questions Answered\n+\n+- The negative-knowledge and merge-risk list is answered and stable.\n+- All prior key questions now have evidence-backed answers.\n+\n+## Questions Remaining\n+\n+- None for this lineage. Exact implementation filenames remain a future implementation choice, not a research blocker.\n+\n+## Convergence Decision\n+\n+- Status: converged.\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.03.\n+- Novelty justification: This pass added only consolidation and contradiction-checking; all substantive asset, structure, ownership, and attribution questions were already answered by iterations 2 and 3.\n+- Stop reason: all key questions answered and novelty below `convergenceThreshold: 0.05`.\n+- Do not run iteration 5 unless a separate lineage or user instruction introduces new source material.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-state.jsonl:1-4\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:17-43\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:72-120\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json:8-44\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json:96-126\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:34-72\n+- .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:17-70\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- newInfoRatio: 0.03\n+- Novelty justification: Consolidation only; no new source class or recommendation axis was discovered.\n+- Confidence: High that the lineage can stop and synthesize.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- What worked and why: The explicit ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix, target metadata, and stack-boundary check converged into one consistent merge shape.\n+- What did not work and why: Running a fifth iteration would likely re-read already-covered evidence instead of answering a remaining question.\n+- What I would do differently: Reserve any further investigation for cross-lineage comparison, not this single lineage.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Run synthesis for this lineage and write `research.md` plus the lineage `resource-map.md`.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Iteration 5 for this lineage is unnecessary unless new evidence is introduced.\n+- Do not treat exact future filenames as a blocker to the research recommendation.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,4 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"iteration\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Convergence and negative knowledge\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.03,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass added only consolidation and contradiction-checking; all substantive asset, structure, ownership, and attribution questions were already answered by iterations 2 and 3.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Final negative-knowledge list consolidated.\",\"No contradictions found across iterations 2 and 3.\",\"Convergence reached below threshold with all key questions answered.\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json\",\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.m