RISKS\n69: \n70: - Avoid bloating `SKILL.md`; adopted data should stay in references/data or optional tooling.\n71: - Keep implementation performance and stack-specific coding guidance aligned with `sk-code` ownership.\n72: - Preserve MIT attribution if any substantial external content is copied or adapted.\n73: - Do not imply current `sk-code` supports stack routes it explicitly does not own today.\n74: - Exact future implementation filenames are not a research blocker.\n75: \n76: ## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\n77: \n78: No blocked-stop events recorded.\n79: \n80: ## 10. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n81: \n82: - graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n83: - graphDecision: converged by question coverage and low novelty, graph convergence not evaluated for this local-source research lineage\n84: - graphBlockers: none recorded\n\n(End of file - total 84 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Auto-generated-style dashboard for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLineage-local dashboard for the `gpt55fast` deep-research run.\n\n## 2. STATUS\n\n- Topic: ui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n- Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z\n- Status: CONVERGED\n- Iteration: 4 of 5\n- Session ID: fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55fast lineage\ndescription: Auto-generated-style dashboard for the gpt-5.5-fast fan-out lineage.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLineage-local dashboard for the `gpt55fast` deep-research run.\n\n## 2. STATUS\n\n- Topic: ui-ux-pro-max merge into sk-interface-design\n- Started: 2026-06-13T16:23:40Z\n- Status: CONVERGED\n- Iteration: 4 of 5\n- Session ID: fanout-gpt55fast-1781367602693-9nehlm\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | External repo inventory and license surface | research | 0.90 | 5 | complete |\n| 2 | Data asset classification and script fit | research | 0.68 | 16 | complete |\n| 3 | House layout, stack ownership, and attribution | research | 0.46 | 10 | complete |\n| 4 | Convergence and negative knowledge | research | 0.03 | 5 | complete |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: 4\n- keyFindings: 10\n- openQuestions: 0\n- resolvedQuestions: 5\n\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n\n- Answered: 5/5\n- [x] Which external asset classes should be ADOPTED, ADAPTED, or SKIPPED for `sk-interface-design`? Evidence: iteration 2 ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix.\n- [x] How should reusable external assets fit the house skill structure without making `SKILL.md` too large? Evidence: iteration 3 recommended house layout.\n- [x] Should stack-specific CSVs be adopted, adapted, or left to `sk-code` ownership? Evidence: iteration 3 stack boundary classification.\n- [x] What license and attribution path is required for mixing MIT external content with the existing Apache-2.0 vendored Anthropic skill? Evidence: iteration 3 mixed-notice path.\n- [x] What negative knowledge and merge risks should the final cross-lineage synthesis preserve? Evidence: iteration 4 negative-knowledge list.\n\n## 5. TREND\n\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.68, 0.46, 0.03\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none recorded\n- convergenceScore: 0.97\n- coverageBySources: {external-root-docs: 5, external-data-csv: 12, external-scripts: 3, external-templates: 3, target-skill: 5, target-license: 1, sk-code: 1, external-stack-csv: 8}\n\n## 6. DEAD ENDS\n\n- Installer/platform-template direct merge: skip direct adoption because it is external distribution plumbing.\n- Direct icon-library preference: skip Phosphor-specific imports as a house default.\n- Direct React performance merge: leave implementation performance to `sk-code`.\n- Wholesale generated design-system corpus merge: use selectively only.\n- Wholesale stack CSV merge: most rows are framework implementation rules, not design direction.\n- Single-license replacement: preserve both Apache-2.0 and MIT notices for mixed-source content.\n- Iteration 5 without new evidence: all questions answered and novelty below threshold.\n\n## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n\nSynthesize this lineage into `research.md` and emit a lineage `resource-map.md`.\n\n## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n\n- Avoid bloating `SKILL.md`; adopted data should stay in references/data or optional tooling.\n- Keep implementation performance and stack-specific coding guidance aligned with `sk-code` ownership.\n- Preserve MIT attribution if any substantial external content is copied or adapted.\n- Do not imply current `sk-code` supports stack routes it explicitly does not own today.\n- Exact future implementation filenames are not a research blocker.\n\n## 9. BLOCKED STOPS\n\nNo blocked-stop events recorded.\n\n## 10. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n\n- graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n- graphDecision: converged by question coverage and low novelty, graph convergence not evaluated for this local-source research lineage\n- graphBlockers: none recorded","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":84,"totalLines":84,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781368923500,"end":1781368923508}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_040c77d71090ac99016a2d885b65888191b1bc38d0e94086c6"}},"id":"prt_ec1dca556001NCLi4Pd1ae2JSB","sessionID":"ses_13e377e8fffeBUJXd02f1iJrmW","messageID":"msg_ec1dc7132001H4q3bZySsT0mO5"}}
