ch/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:29-52]\n16: - No contradiction was found between script adaptation and runtime restraint. Iteration 2 classifies search/generator scripts as optional tooling; iteration 3 says runtime routing should not make Python search or generator execution mandatory. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:29-31] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:20-21]\n17: - No contradiction was found between stack guidance value and ownership. Iteration 2 already skipped direct React performance merge; iteration 3 broadened that into a stack-boundary rule after checking representative stack CSVs and current `sk-code` scope. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:27-28] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:22-25]\n18: - The final negative knowledge is stable: do not merge external installer/platform plumbing; do not dump data into `SKILL.md`; do not replace `design_principles.md`; do not make external generators mandatory; do not prefer Phosphor icons; do not absorb React/stack implementation rules into `sk-interface-design`; do not assume current `sk-code` owns generic stacks; do not collapse Apache-2.0 and MIT notices. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:72-120]\n19: - The only residual uncertainty is naming, not substance: a future implementation packet can choose exact names (`references/design_intelligence/`, `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`, `scripts/design_lookup.py`) while preserving the same architectural recommendation. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:29-52]\n20: \n21: ## Final Negative Knowledge\n22: \n23: - Do not edit `.opencode/skills/sk-interface-design/` in this research lineage.\n24: - Do not merge the external installer, marketplace, CLI, or platform-template plumbing.\n25: - Do not inline large CSVs or generated design-system text into `SKILL.md`.\n26: - Do not replace the Anthropic-derived `references/design_principles.md`; keep it as the primary authority.\n27: - Do not make `search.py`, `core.py`, or `design_system.py` mandatory runtime steps.\n28: - Do not use `design_system.py --persist` as a default house workflow because it writes separate design-system documents.\n29: - Do not make Phosphor the default icon system for all projects.\n30: - Do not absorb React/Next/React Native/SwiftUI/Flutter implementation checklists into `sk-interface-design`.\n31: - Do not imply current `sk-code` already supports those generic stack routes.\n32: - Do not use `ui-reasoning.csv` as deterministic truth; it should guide, not override the brief and critique process.\n33: - Do not collapse Apache-2.0 and MIT material under one unqualified license label.\n34: \n35: ## Questions Answered\n36: \n37: - The negative-knowledge and merge-risk list is answered and stable.\n38: - All prior key questions now have evidence-backed answers.\n39: \n40: ## Questions Remaining\n41: \n42: - None for this lineage. Exact implementation filenames remain a future implementation choice, not a research blocker.\n43: \n44: ## Convergence Decision\n45: \n46: - Status: converged.\n47: - newInfoRatio: 0.03.\n48: - Novelty justification: This pass added only consolidation and contradiction-checking; all substantive asset, structure, ownership, and attribution questions were already answered by iterations 2 and 3.\n49: - Stop reason: all key questions answered and novelty below `convergenceThreshold: 0.05`.\n50: - Do not run iteration 5 unless a separate lineage or user instruction introduces new source material.\n51: \n52: ## Sources Consulted\n53: \n54: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-state.jsonl:1-4\n55: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:17-43\n56: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:72-120\n57: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json:8-44\n58: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json:96-126\n59: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:34-72\n60: - .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:17-70\n61: \n62: ## Assessment\n63: \n64: - newInfoRatio: 0.03\n65: - Novelty justification: Consolidation only; no new source class or recommendation axis was discovered.\n66: - Confidence: High that the lineage can stop and synthesize.\n67: \n68: ## Reflection\n69: \n70: - What worked and why: The explicit ADOPT/ADAPT/SKIP matrix, target metadata, and stack-boundary check converged into one consistent merge shape.\n71: - What did not work and why: Running a fifth iteration would likely re-read already-covered evidence instead of answering a remaining question.\n72: - What I would do differently: Reserve any further investigation for cross-lineage comparison, not this single lineage.\n73: \n74: ## Recommended Next Focus\n75: \n76: Run synthesis for this lineage and write `research.md` plus the lineage `resource-map.md`.\n77: \n78: ## Dead Ends\n79: \n80: - Iteration 5 for this lineage is unnecessary unless new evidence is introduced.\n81: - Do not treat exact future filenames as a blocker to the research recommendation.\n\n(End of file - total 81 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 4: Convergence And Negative Knowledge\n\n## Focus\n\nConsolidate the final negative knowledge and merge-risk list, then determine whether further iterations are likely to add enough new information to justify running to iteration 5.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n- Read the current state log, strategy, findings registry, and prior iteration reports.\n- Checked the open questions against answered questions and ruled-out directions.\n- Compared iteration 2 asset classification with iteration 3 structure, stack ownership, and attribution recommendations.\n\n## Findings\n\n- No contradiction was found between the asset classification and the house-structure recommendation. Iteration 2 says high-value external content should be adopted as data/reference assets, and iteration 3 gives that content a separate optional `references/design_intelligence/` subtree rather than changing the primary design process. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:34-53] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:29-52]\n- No contradiction was found between script adaptation and runtime restraint. Iteration 2 classifies search/generator scripts as optional tooling; iteration 3 says runtime routing should not make Python search or generator execution mandatory. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:29-31] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:20-21]\n- No contradiction was found between stack guidance value and ownership. Iteration 2 already skipped direct React performance merge; iteration 3 broadened that into a stack-boundary rule after checking representative stack CSVs and current `sk-code` scope. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-002.md:27-28] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/iterations/iteration-003.md:22-25]\n- The final negative knowledge is stable: do not merge external installer/platform plumbing; do not dump data into `SKILL.md`; do not replace `design_principles.md`; do not make external generators mandatory; do not prefer Phosphor icons; do not absorb React/stack implementation rules into `sk-interface-design`; do not assume current `sk-code` owns generic stacks; do not collapse Apache-2.0 and MIT notices. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md:72-120]\n- The only residual uncertainty is naming, not substance: a future implementation packet can choose exact names (`references/design_intelligence/`, `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`, `scripts/design_lookup.py`) while preserving the same architectural recommendation. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/002-ui-ux-pro-max-merge-research/rese